---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import { withBase } from '../lib/paths';

// Public privacy policy (sign-off-ledger gate; ethics-equity-checklist §2.1).
// Discloses exactly what is collected, why, and how to delete it. MVP scope:
// no payments, no third-party advertising, no email marketing.
const updated = 'June 12, 2026';
const contactEmail = 'hello@thoughtfuldesign.io';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Privacy Policy — Thoughtful Design"
  description="What Thoughtful Design collects, why, and how to access or delete your data."
>
  <article class="container legal">
    <header class="legal__head">
      <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
      <p class="muted">Last updated {updated}</p>
    </header>

    <div class="prose legal__body">
      <p>
        Thoughtful Design is a self-led online course. This policy explains exactly what
        information we collect when you create an account and use the course, why we collect
        it, and how you can access or delete it. We keep this short and specific on purpose.
      </p>

      <h2>What we collect</h2>
      <p>We only collect what the course needs to work and to track your progress:</p>
      <table class="legal__table">
        <thead>
          <tr><th>Data</th><th>Why we collect it</th></tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr>
            <td><strong>Email address</strong></td>
            <td>To create and secure your account and to let you sign in.</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td><strong>Display name</strong></td>
            <td>To greet you in the app and to print your name on your certificate.</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td><strong>Lesson progress</strong></td>
            <td>Which lessons you have completed and any reflection notes you save, so you can resume where you left off.</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td><strong>Quiz responses</strong></td>
            <td>Your answers to the inline checks in each lesson, so we can show feedback and track your learning.</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td><strong>Assessment attempts</strong></td>
            <td>Your scores on module, milestone, and final assessments, so we can show pass/fail status and unlock your certificate.</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td><strong>Certificate record</strong></td>
            <td>The date your certificate was issued and whether it was awarded with distinction.</td>
          </tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
      <p>
        We also record a small number of <strong>product analytics events</strong> (for example,
        when a lesson is started or completed, an assessment is passed, or a certificate is
        issued) so we can understand whether the course is working as a learning tool. These
        events are tied to your account while you are signed in.
      </p>

      <h2>What we do not do</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>We do <strong>not</strong> sell your personal data to third parties.</li>
        <li>We do <strong>not</strong> share your data with advertisers or run ad tracking.</li>
        <li>We do <strong>not</strong> send marketing email. Account email (such as a password reset) is transactional only.</li>
        <li>We do <strong>not</strong> collect payment information in this version of the course.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>How your data is stored</h2>
      <p>
        Your account and progress are stored using <a href="https://supabase.com/privacy" rel="noopener noreferrer">Supabase</a>,
        our database and authentication provider, acting as a data processor on our behalf.
        Access is restricted so that you can only read and write your own records.
      </p>

      <h2>Accessing and deleting your data</h2>
      <p>
        You can delete your learning data at any time from your
        <a href={withBase('/account')}>account settings</a>. Deleting your account removes your
        profile, lesson progress, reflection notes, quiz responses, assessment attempts,
        certificate record, and analytics events.
      </p>
      <p>
        If you would like a copy of your data, or you want us to confirm full removal of your
        sign-in record, email <a href={`mailto:${contactEmail}`}>{contactEmail}</a> and we will
        respond within 30 days.
      </p>

      <h2>Children</h2>
      <p>
        Thoughtful Design is built for working professionals and is not intended for anyone
        under 18. We do not knowingly collect data from children.
      </p>

      <h2>Changes to this policy</h2>
      <p>
        If we change what we collect or how we use it, we will update this page and revise the
        date above. Questions? Email <a href={`mailto:${contactEmail}`}>{contactEmail}</a>.
      </p>
    </div>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .legal {
    padding: 2.5rem 0 3.5rem;
    max-width: var(--content-width);
  }

  .legal__head {
    margin-bottom: 1.75rem;
    padding-bottom: 1.25rem;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border);
  }

  .legal__head h1 {
    font-family: var(--font-serif);
    margin: 0 0 0.35rem;
  }

  .legal__body h2 {
    font-family: var(--font-serif);
    margin-top: 2.25rem;
  }

  .legal__table {
    width: 100%;
    border-collapse: collapse;
    margin: 1rem 0;
    font-size: 0.95rem;
  }

  .legal__table th,
  .legal__table td {
    text-align: left;
    vertical-align: top;
    padding: 0.6rem 0.75rem;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border);
  }

  .legal__table th {
    color: var(--muted);
    font-size: 0.85rem;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.04em;
  }
</style>
